<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 4:28AM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...INCREASING SNOWFALL RATES THIS MORNING...
Doppler radar is indicating bands of heavy snowfall located across
the area which will continue for the next few hours. Snowfall
rates of 1 to 2 inches per hour are likely within these bands.
This will result in hazardous travel on any untreated surfaces.
Visibilities in these snow bands are also reduced to around one
half mile. If you must travel early this morning, allow extra
time.</description>
